Text
Croatian Central Finance and Contracting Agency (CFCA) is seeking to contract:
Resident Twinning Advisor (RTA) Assistant (1 person)
for the European Union funded Twinning project “Further support to Indirect Taxation Authority of Bosnia and Herzegovina.”
The project is implemented by the consortium of Croatian and Slovenian institutions and the final beneficiary of the project is the Indirect Taxation Authority of Bosnia and Hercegovina (ITA BiH). The project focuses on strengthening of administrative capacities of the ITA of Bosnia and Herzegovina, particularly in the areas of customs procedures, VAT and excise duties administration, risk management and data exchange.
The fixed-term service contract is expected to cover the period from 1 September 2026 to 29 February 2028, subject to the official start date of the project. The
full-time
role shall be performed at the premises of the Indirect Taxation Authority of Bosnia and Hercegovina in Banja Luka.
The person must be an Bosnian and Herzegovinian national or have valid residence and work permits to work in the Bosnia and Herzegovina.
The maximum gross monthly salary offered is
2.000,00 EUR
(non-negotiable).
The selected person will be a self-employed independent consultant under a Service Contract and will undertake full responsibility for the payment of all taxes and obligations deriving from the legislation in force in the Bosnia and Herzegovina including those related to medical and social insurance.
The selected person shall not have been in contractual relation with Bosnia and Herzegovina public sector during at least six (6) months preceding their hiring.
RTA ASSISTANT (1 person)
REQUIREMENTS:
University degree, preferably in English;
Full professional fluency in English (spoken and written);
Native or equivalent proficiency in Bosnian/Croatian/Serbian (spoken and written);
Computer literacy (MS Office, Internet, email etc.);
Flexibility to work independently and as a part of a team;
Excellent organizational, inter-personal and communication skills;
Understanding of financial management;
Strong drafting and reporting skills.
ASSETS:
Experience in EU funded projects, especially in Twinning projects;
Previous experience of working in an international environment;
Knowledge of Bosnia and Herzegovina public sector and/or Bosnia and Herzegovina system in the area of the project;
Experience in translation and/or interpretation from Bosnian/Croatian/Serbian into English and vice versa;
Experience in translation and/or interpretation of customs/tax-related or legal documents;
Knowledge of Croatian (and/or Slovenian) language.
TASKS / JOB DESCRIPTION:
Providing day-to-day administrative and coordination support to the RTA;
Providing interpretation services for the RTA and for short-term experts;
Providing translation of relevant project-related written material from Bosnian/Croatian/Serbian to English and vice versa;
Assisting visiting short-term experts, Project Leader, Junior Project Leader and Component Leaders when needed;
Providing general management support, including office management and correspondence;
Assisting in project co-ordination and project management;
Assisting in writing and editing project documents and financial tables;
Developing and maintaining close working contacts and relationships with Beneficiary Country officials and staff, EUD as well as Croatian and Slovenian partner institutions;
Assisting in organization of meetings, seminars and workshops;
Preparing meeting agendas, writing and editing minutes of meetings;
Assisting in the organization of visibility events, preparation of the needed documents and promotional materials; writing information about the project for general public or targeted stakeholders;
Supporting the organisation of study visits to Croatia and Slovenia, including logistical arrangements and, where necessary, accompanying and assisting participants;
Arranging travel and booking accommodation;
Perform other tasks as assigned by the RTA.
Interested candidates are requested to submit their
CV and a cover letter
in English via e-mail to the following addresses:
thea.soldo@safu.hr
and
twinning@safu.hr
by 15 July 2026.
Only shortlisted candidates will be invited for an interview. Interviews will be held on-line
.
For any further information please contact the abovementioned e-mail addresses.

We offer
The post of Driver (Local Agent, Group V) in the Delegation’s Administration Section. The team consists of 8 people and there are occasional typical working hours. The team works closely with the Head of Delegation.
Under this post, the recruited person will be attributed functions depending on the needs of the Delegation, and on the changes of these needs. The successful candidate
will serve under the supervision and responsibility
of the Head of Section, providing support, expertise and assistance in administrative support as regards financial management and related matters in compliance with EU Financial Regulation and other legal requirements, administrative support for the section.
Following main tasks and duties are currently required:
To ensure the transportation for the Delegation and car maintenance;
To ensuring the transportation of the staff in the execution of their official duties including missions inside and outside of the Country;
To ensure the transportation of visitors during their missions;
To deliver in due time messages, mails, pouch etc.;
To be responsible for the cleaning and maintenance of the vehicles fleet;
To assist in the customs procedures when requested;
To report on a regular basis: log book and repairs made on vehicles;
To assist in administrative matters;
To provide manpower;
To fulfill any other related tasks as requested by line manager in the interest of service;
The base salary will depend on relevant and verified employment experience, typically starting from
KZT 341,126.
There is a competitive benefits package, subject to certain conditions, including personal leave days and public holidays, health insurances and a retirement savings plan.
The expected start date will be 15 February 2024.
Minimum requirements / eligibility criteria (necessary for the application to be considered)
Medically fit to perform the required duties;
Enjoys civil rights and permits for employment under local law;
Minimum of 3 years of experience as a driver, or related administrative position (courier service, etc.)
Excellent knowledge of English (B2), Kazakh (B1) and Russian C1 (speaking and writing) ;
B driving license since at least 2 years;
Knowledge of Microsoft Office.
Assets / selection criteria (basis for awarding points to select the best applicant)
C or D driving license;
Working knowledge of other EU language(s);
How to apply
Please submit your
application, consisting of a cover letter and a detailed CV Europass format ONLY (
https://europa.eu/europass/en/create-europass-cv
) and a declaration of honour regarding the work rights and medical fitness (according to the template attached)
via
Delegation-Kazakhstan-Vacancies@eeas.europa.eu
(Reference: Budget/Accounting Assistant post) no later than
07/02/2024, at 17:00hrs (Astana time).
Only complete applications received on time via email will be considered.
The successful candidate will be subject to a medical check.
The process
After the deadline for applications, the
eligible
applications will be admitted to the Selection by the Committee set up for this purpose.
Depending on the number of applications received, successive phases of Selection may include shortlisting of candidates based on the assessment of the information provided in the cover letter and CV, practical testing (written) and interviews. At least
3
best candidates will be invited to the final interview.
Only candidates admitted to each successive selection phase will be contacted individually. The Delegation will use the same means of publication as for this job advertisement to inform the remaining candidates once the recruitment procedure has been completed and that a candidate has (or has not) been recruited.
The Delegation will not supply additional information or discuss the selection procedure. During the selection process, please do not contact the members of the Selection Committee, but address your questions and comments to the Delegation’s Administration via
Delegation-Kazakhstan-Vacancies@eeas.europa.eu
.

Text
We are
The European Union (EU) is an economic and political partnership between 27 European countries. It plays an important role in international affairs through diplomacy, trade, development aid and working with global organizations. Abroad, the EU is represented through more than 140 diplomatic representations, known also as EU Delegations, which have a similar function to those of an embassy.
The EU Delegation to Thailand
works in close coordination with the Embassies and Consulates of the 27 EU Member States. We are a fully-fledged diplomatic mission and represent the European Union in dealings with the Thai government in areas that are part of the EU’s remit.
We offer
The post of Secretary/Protocol (Local Agent Group 3) in the Administration Section. The team consists of 20 people and there are occasional atypical working hours.
Under this post, the recruited person will be attributed functions depending on the needs of the Delegation, and on the changes of these needs. The successful candidate will serve under the supervision and responsibility of the Head of Administration Section, providing support, expertise and assistance to the Section.
Functions and duties:
Responsible for Expats and their family, household member, and their new born baby in relation to their arrival, visa, temporary accommodation provided that they require, their termination, permit of stay; re-entry visa, I.D. cards, driving license;
Protocol, permit to stay, re-entry, driving licence, ID card (including new, renewal, loss, damage), car sale, car purchase, car registration and renewal;
Update of diplomatic list;
Update Post report for the new comers;
Visa prior authorisation, visa on missions;
Keep track/update the list of expat, family and household member in terms of renewal protocol issues on daily basis;
Airport pass renewal both Donmuang and Suvarnabhumi Airports;
Request for a license with MFA during VIP, bodyguards' arrival with weapon;
Serviced vehicles on selling / buying / importation / plate registration and plate renewal (Back up);
Issuance/add/change the authenticated signature of authorized expats signing documents (Back up);
Customs formalities, personal effects, car, pets, etc.;
Contacts and preparation of documents concerning customs clearance procedures on importation of goods; personal effects; purchase or sales of service and private vehicles for officials, Contract Agents; Junior Experts, Individual Experts;
Shipment of EUDEL DHL’s diplomatic cargo through DHL (Back up);
Shipment of Liquor/alcohol clearance (Back up);
Issuance correspondence such as opening bank account letter, residence letter, working certificate, invitation letter for visa, and others as required;
Filing and upkeeping of the filing system and archives of the Administration;
License/disposal X-ray machine and new license, and OSL film renewal to Ministry of Science and Atoms for Peace (Back up);
To undertake other assignments that may be requested in view of the efficient functioning of the Section or the Delegation.
The base salary will depend on relevant and verified employment experience, typically starting from a minimum of 66,903 Baht per month. There is a competitive benefits package, subject to certain conditions, including a 13
th
month salary, provident fund, transportation allowance, child allowance, 20 days of annual leave, and public holidays, as well as health insurance (The salary is subject to local taxes).
Minimum requirements / eligibility criteria (necessary for the application to be considered)
Must hold a higher education and/or a degree in secretarial work;
5 years of relevant executive secretarial / office experience;
Experience with Embassy – MFA relations is an asset;
Experience with Embassy – Immigration/Customs/Department of Land Transport/Airport of Thailand/Shipping agents relations is an asset.
Good command of Thai and English (written and spoken);
Excellent oral and written communications skills with external and internal contacts;
Computer literate (and knowledge of commonly used programs such as Word, Excel).
Assets / selection criteria (basis for awarding points to select the best applicant)
Able to work as a team member with good inter-personal skills;
Ability to work in a multicultural environment;
Ability to negotiate at all level, ability of negotiate within various Thai Authorities in a multicultural and multilingual environment;
Ability to understand and contribute to effective and efficient administration and procedures of the Admin team;
Capacity to focus on priorities and to organize work to deliver on time;
Attention to detail and accuracy;
Capable of producing high quality results within often tight deadlines;
Knowledge of European Union, its rules and functioning is an asset.

Text
We are
The European Union (EU) is an economic and political partnership between 27 European countries. It plays an important role in international affairs through diplomacy, trade, development aid and working with global organizations. Abroad, the EU is represented through more than 140 diplomatic representations, known also as EU Delegations, which have a similar function to those of an embassy.
The EU Delegation to Thailand
works in close coordination with the Embassies and Consulates of the 27 EU Member States. We are a fully-fledged diplomatic mission and represent the European Union in dealings with the Thai government in areas that are part of the EU’s remit.
We offer
The post of Handyman/Driver (Local Agent Group 5) in the Administration Section. The team consists of 20 people and there are occasional atypical working hours.
Under this post, the recruited person will be attributed functions depending on the needs of the Delegation, and on the changes of these needs. The successful candidate will serve under the supervision and responsibility of the Head of Delegation, Deputy Head of Delegation, Administration section, and other sections and providing support, expertise and assistance to the Delegation.
Functions and duties:
To drive for Delegation’s staff as per assignment;
To comply with all the existing law, rules and regulations issued for the road especially the speed limit;
To drive in a safe manner that ensures passengers safety and vehicle longevity;
The service car under his responsibility should be well maintained and taken care of;
Making photocopies;
Assist in preparing the diplomatic pouches;
Contacts with local authorities, Customs, Airport of Thailand, Thai Immigration, Department of Land Transport, and various ministries;
Meeting rooms set up;
Buy office supplies;
Making photocopies;
Assist in preparing the diplomatic pouches;
Minor repair in EUDEL office and minor internal removal of items and furniture.
The base salary will depend on relevant and verified employment experience, typically starting from a minimum of 31,560 Baht per month. There is a competitive benefits package, subject to certain conditions, including a 13
th
month salary, provident fund, transportation allowance, child allowance, 20 days of annual leave, and public holidays, as well as health insurance (The salary is subject to local taxes).
Minimum requirements / eligibility criteria (necessary for the application to be considered)
Must hold a secondary school and/or higher;
5 years of driving experience of which at least 3 years with embassy or international organisation and with valid driving licence;
Familiarity with location of Embassies, Ministries, International Organizatins and others, within Bangkok;
Ability to speak and understand English.
Assets / selection criteria (basis for awarding points to select the best applicant)
Some knowledge of mechanics of vehicles;
Good communication skills with external and internal contacts;
Knowledge of computer skills i.e. Word, Excel, E-mail and Internet;
Able to work as a team member;
Ability to work in a multicultural environment;
Ability to understand and contribute to effective and efficient administration and procedures of the Delegation;
Capable to execute tasks in a timely and efficient manner.

The European Union Delegation to the Lao PDR is looking for:
Secretary (Local Agent Group III) in the Delegation’s Cooperation Section
We are
The European Union (EU) is an economic and political partnership between 27 European countries. It plays an important role in international affairs through diplomacy, trade, development aid and working with global organisations. Abroad, the EU is represented through more than 140 diplomatic representations, known also as EU Delegations, which have a similar function to those of an embassy.
The EU Delegation to the Lao PDR aims to strengthen EU-Lao PDR relations and is a major development partner for Lao PDR.
We offer
We offer a post of Secretary within the Cooperation section. Under this post, the recruited person will be attributed functions depending on the needs of the Delegation. Upon recruitment, the successful candidate will occupy a specific job function as Secretary. She/he will provide administrative, secretarial and logistic support to the Head of Cooperation and Programme Managers to support the functioning of the cooperation section and a smooth implementation of EU – Lao PDR cooperation. This job function may be changed in accordance with the needs of the Delegation.
Following main tasks and duties are currently required:
Overall organizational and administrative assistance in the Cooperation section;
Agenda management of the section;
Drafting of correspondence and meeting minutes including assistance with translations;
Formatting, editing, and synthesizing of reports and documents;
Maintenance of section files; classification, filing, and registering of correspondence and documents;
Logistical support to the organization of meetings/events/missions;
Relations with external stakeholders regarding events and public affairs;
Maintenance of Lao counterparts mailing lists and update contact details;
Preparation of incoming and outgoing missions;
Making travel arrangements for members of the section’s official travels;
Ad hoc tasks relating to the activities of the Section and the Delegation.
The base salary will depend on relevant and verified employment experience, typically starting from EUR 714 but can be higher in accordance with relevant professional experience. There is a competitive benefits package, subject to certain conditions, including personal leave days and public holidays, health insurances and a retirement savings plan.
The expected start date will be 1st October 2024.
Minimum requirements / eligibility criteria (necessary for the application to be considered)
Minimum of completed secondary level education;
Minimum of 2 years of experience in relevant field is desirable;
Native level command of Lao language (C2 level) and good knowledge of English (B2 oral and written level);
Excellent knowledge of computer applications: Excel, MS Office software, Word, PowerPoint, scheduling and communication;
Right to residence and work in Lao PDR.
Assets / selection criteria (basis for awarding points to select the best applicant)
University degree or equivalent in a relevant field (Business Administration, English language, International Relations, etc..);
Previous experience working in an Embassy or international organisation as secretary/ administrative staff;
Ability to work as a team member with good inter-personal skills and to work in a multicultural environment;
Excellent communications and presentation skills;
C1 level in English: oral and written expression.
How to apply
Please submit your application, consisting of a cover letter expressing your motivation, Europass format CV
https://europass.europa.eu/en
and a declaration on honour regarding the civil rights and permits for employment under local law in Laos and medical fitness (no template, free format), via the Functional Mailbox
eeasjobs-134@eeas.europa.eu
(Reference/subject: NAME – Application for LA-3 post Secretary) no later than
16:00 on 9 September 2024
. Only complete applications received on time via the Functional Mailbox
eeasjobs-134@eeas.europa.eu
will be considered.
The successful candidate will be subject to a medical check and background check.
The process
After the deadline for applications, the eligible applications will be admitted to the Selection by the Committee set up for this purpose.
Depending on the number of applications received, successive phases of Selection may include shortlisting of candidates based assessment of the information provided in the cover letter and CV; practical testing and interviews. The 3 best candidates will be invited to the final phase.
Only candidates admitted to each successive selection phase will be contacted individually. The Delegation will use the same means of publication as for this job advertisement to inform the remaining candidates once the recruitment procedure has been completed and that a candidate has (or has not) been recruited.
The Delegation will not supply additional information or discuss the selection procedure. During the selection process, please do not contact the members of the Selection Committee, but address your questions and comments to
eeasjobs-134@eeas.europa.eu
.

WE ARE
The European External Action Service (EEAS) is the European Union’s diplomatic service. Since 2011, the EEAS carries out the EU’s Common Foreign and Security Policy (CFSP) to promote peace, prosperity, security, and the interests of the EU across the globe. It brings together European civil servants, diplomats from EU Member States, national experts and local staff worldwide.The EEAS supports the High Representative in the exercise of her mandate to steer the Union’s CFSP, including the Common Security and Defence Policy (CSDP), to represent the EU on issues relating to the CFSP and to chair the Foreign Affairs Council. It also supports her as Vice-President of the Commission with regard to her responsibilities within the Commission, including the coordination of other aspects of the EU’s external action. The EEAS works in close cooperation with the EU Member States, the General Secretariat of the Council, the services of the Commission and the Secretariat General of the European Parliament.
The EEAS Headquarters are in Brussels. It is also responsible for the management of the network of 145 Union Delegations and Offices worldwide. These Diplomatic Representations play a vital role in representing the EU in the country where they are based, in promoting the values and interests of the EU, and in building networks and partnerships. They are responsible for all policy areas of the relationship between the EU and the host country/organisation.
The EEAS Managing Directorate (MD) for Africa, including five divisions and 46 delegations, supports the High Representative and Vice President of the Commission (HRVP) in defining and implementing the EU's Common Foreign and Security Policy in Africa.
WE PROPOSE
The position of Secretary to the Director/Deputy Managing Director (DMD), as a contract agent FGII as per article 3b of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Union (hereafter, the “CEOS”).
The selected candidate will be the Secretary to the Deputy Managing Director and will have primary responsibility for the management of their agenda and administration. They will also collaborate with the Political assistant to the Managing Director and with the administrative assistant as part of a team of three who jointly support the smooth functioning of the whole Managing Directorate.
Subject to having passed the CAST exam, the successful candidate will be offered a contract agent position (Function group II), on the basis of a contract with an initial duration of one year that may be successively renewed up to a maximum duration of six years, subject to the maximum duration of engagement by the EEAS allowed under successive limited duration contracts of different types.
PLACE and DATE OF EMPLOYMENT
‎EEAS Headquarters, Brussels, Belgium
Post available: 1 September 2026
LEGAL BASIS FOR RECRUITMENT TO THIS POSITION
The vacancy is to be filled in accordance with the conditions stipulated under the CEOS, in particular Article 82 thereof.
WE LOOK FOR
A dynamic, flexible and proactive colleague with good communication and organisational skills with a developed sense of service. The Secretary should be able to quickly adapt to new working environment and be a good team-player. The successful candidate should have very good computer skills, a sound knowledge of the standard IT applications and administrative procedures used in the EAAS. They will be entrusted with the following main tasks:
Provide efficient secretarial support;
Provide overall administrative support to the Deputy Managing Director (DMD);
Coordinate the administrative and financial procedures and processes;
Deliver the expected outputs and achieve the objectives required by the DMD in accordance with existing rules governing the EEAS administration;
Carry out various administrative tasks such as diary-keeping, overview of deadlines for DMD Africa tasks and coordination with the secretaries of the MD and of the Divisions, filtering telephone calls, filing and ordering supplies, dealing with correspondence;
Document management: registration of incoming and outgoing correspondence, including in Ares;
Manage functional mailboxes and send requested information and documents;
Organise missions of DMD Africa using MIPS application;
Organise meetings, events and incoming visits;
Support the DMD in the overall management of Human resources processes
Co-ordinate the creation, keeping up to date and retrieval of documents and data in the appropriate files or IT databases (Hive);
Assist with the preparation of briefing files, speeches, etc;
Facilitate communication within the Africa Department, within the EEAS, as well as with external partners;
Act as back-up for the Secretary to the Managing Director and for the administrative assistant when needed.
Eligibility criteria
Further to the conditions set out in Article 82 of the CEOS, candidates must:
have passed a valid EPSO CAST in a valid function group for this post, or be registered in the EPSO Permanent CAST in a valid function group for this post (
https://eu-careers.europa.eu/en/contract-staff-selection-procedures-always-open-registration
). In the latter case, while the registration will make the candidate eligible for the selection procedure, the recruitment of a candidate on this vacant post will be subject to his/her successfully passing the CAST exam;
have a level of post-secondary education attested by a diploma or a level of secondary education attested by a diploma giving access to post-secondary education and appropriate professional experience of three year;
have the capacity to work in the languages of the CFSP and external relations (English and French) necessary for the performance of their duties;
be a national of one of the Member States of the European Union and enjoy full rights as a citizen.
Selection criteria
Candidates should have:
Proven experience in the secretariat field. Experience in the field of external relations will be an asset;
Experience in treatment of classified and sensitive information;
Experience in operational and administrative support;
Experience in resources, information and document management;
Adaptability to new working environment and be a good team player;
Very good computer skills (MS Office) and good knowledge of standard administrative procedures;
Ability to perform multiple tasks, to adjust to changing priorities, pressing deadlines, perform tasks autonomously and ensure good coordination with the other secretaries and with the Divisions;
Very good knowledge of English and French in oral and written form supported by recognised experience in using them as main working languages;
good inter-personal skills, excellent team working spirit, flexibility to accept when needed long working hours and availability to work mainly in presence mode;
Furthermore:
Experience of working in a team in multi-disciplinary and multi-cultural environment;
Experience in working with or within other EU institutions and/or in EU Delegations;
A certain level of understanding of the region in the remit of the Directorate as well as exposure to Diplomacy
will be considered as strong assets.
CONDITIONS OF RECRUITMENT AND EMPLOYMENT
CONFLICT OF INTEREST AND SECURITY RISKS
As a matter of policy, applications by individuals who have dual nationality, of which one of a non-EU country, will be considered on a case-by-case basis taking account in particular of the functions attributed to the vacant post. The EEAS also examines if there could be a conflict of interest or security risks.
In this context,
all candidates shall fill with their application a
declaration of potential conflict of interest
.
MEDICAL CLEARANCE
The signature of the contract will be subject to prior favourable opinion of the Medical Service, unless the successful candidate is a temporary agent currently employed in the EEAS.
PERSONNEL SECURITY CLEARANCE
(hereafter, “PSC”)
The requested level of security clearance for this post is: SECRET UE/EU SECRET. A description of the EU classified information levels is available under Article 2 of Annex A of the
Decision ADMIN(2023) 18 on the security rules of the EEAS
.
The selected candidate should hold, or be in the position to obtain, a valid Personnel Security Clearance (hereafter, the “PSC”) issued by the competent authority of the Member State concerned.
Candidates who do not already have a valid PSC will be required to go through the security clearance vetting procedure of their Member State to obtain this clearance in accordance with national laws and regulations and with the procedure laid down in the
Decision ADMIN(2025) 42 on Implementing Rules and Procedures for Personnel Security measures for protection of EU Classified Information of 20 November 2025
and in Annex A I of the
Decision ADMIN(2023) 18 on the security rules of the EEAS
. Until the PSC is issued by the competent authority of the Member State concerned, the selected candidate will not be authorised to access EUCI at the level of CONFIDENTIEL UE/EU CONFIDENTIAL or above, or to participate in any meetings or workflow where EUCI is processed.
Please note that the necessary procedure for obtaining a PSC can be initiated on request of the employer only, and not by the individual candidate.
In case of failure to obtain or renew the required PSC, the AACC may take the appropriate measures in accordance with Article 7 of the
Decision ADMIN(2025) 42 on Implementing Rules and Procedures for Personnel Security measures for protection of EU Classified Information of 20 November 2025.
EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES
The EEAS strives to be a dynamic, respectful and inclusive Service. We value the talent and professional excellence of our staff, and are committed to building an organisation where gender equality and the respect of diversity are core values, as set out in the EEAS Mission Statement and the EEAS Agenda for Diversity and Inclusion. The EEAS is committed to achieving gender balance within its workforce an
